<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06248198 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06248198 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  ROBBERY; SHOOTING  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  As one robber held a knife to his throat and another covered him with asawed-off shotgun, a store owner managed to pull a pistol and kill them both,along with a third bandit.;   Jaime Alonso, 30, owner of the San Luis Outpost,a bait and gun shop on Highway 152 a mile west of Los Banos, and his employee,Bennie Cotter, 62, were unhurt.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  California News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  LOS BANOS STORE OWNER FATALLY SHOOTS 3 ROBBERS ASTHEY HOLD HIM CAPTIVE  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     A fourth robber escaped during the 5 p.m. robbery attempt, said Lt. BillBlake of the Merced County Sheriff's Department.;   Authorities were trying todetermine the identities of the three robbers who died at the scene.;   Thefourth man escaped unharmed in a stolen white pickup truck. A statewidebulletin was broadcast warning that the man was armed and dangerous.;   Themen bought food and beer at the store at 3 p.m. and returned two hours laterwith the intent to rob the store, Blake said.;   The suspects had returned ina car reported stolen from Riverside County, he said. They waited for severalother customers to leave the store before pulling their weapons.;   One manproduced a 12-gauge shotgun and pointed it at Alonso from across the counter.;  A second suspect went behind the counter, pulled out a knife and held it toAlonso's throat.;   A third suspect went behind an adjoining counter, whichwas loaded with guns and ammunition for sale, and began taking guns.;   WhenCotter, who was in a back storage room, came out, the fourth man begansearching him, Blake said.;   Alonso, saying he was in fear for his life,asked if he could sit down near the cash register. On a nearby shelf was aloaded 9mm automatic handgun, Blake said.;   Apparently the commotion betweenCotter and the fourth suspect distracted the others, and Alonso grabbed thegun and shot the man with the shotgun.;   The man ran out of the store and wasfound dead 10 feet outside the door, Blake said.;   Alonso then shot the manwith the knife and the man behind the adjoining counter.;   The suspect withCotter ran to a nearby flea market, where he stole a truck and fled west onHighway 152, Blake said.;   No charges against Alonso were anticipated, Blakesaid.;   &quot;There is nothing that would indicate that he acted improperly,&quot;Blake said.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  McClatchy News Service  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Los BaNos  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910904  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  384  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, September 4, 199100248198,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>